03Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΘΟΝΙ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":105,"ptr":162,"ref":163,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},{"target":107},{"_":109,"target":109},{"file":165,"uri":165,"title":166,"status":167,"editionAuthor":13,"type":168,"objectType":169,"material":173,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":174,"handNote":178,"date":196,"places":199,"geo":205,"provenance":201,"provenanceGeo":209,"country":69,"region":70,"settlement":71,"repository":212,"idno":213,"textLang":215,"tmNumber":26,"facsimile":217,"letterHeights":224,"publications":225,"zotero":226,"keywords":227,"html":232,"bibl":233},"ISic001871","Funerary inscription for Gamike",{"_":12},{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},{"_":170,"ana":171,"ref":172},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},{"layout":175},{"p":176,"rs":177,"damage":26},"Text over five lines, carefully following guidelines to the base of each line, with a marginal guideline to the left and right, with the left margin consistently observed. An additional guideline below is unused; the guidelines carefully align with the text to the right of this one. Use of a vacat prior to the age at death.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"lettering":179,"dimensions":180},"Deep and wide slightly crude v-cut, producing consistent fairly square letters without serifs. Alpha has mostly downward left sloping cross-bar; epsilon is lunate with mostly shorter middle bar; zeta has slight curvature to the strokes; kappa has short arms; mu has four full-length diagonal strokes; lunate sigma, but note final square lunate for digamma / stigma for numeral 6.",[181,183,186,188,192,195],{"type":38,"l":134,"from":40,"to":40,"h":182,"unit":43},"27-30",{"type":38,"l":184,"from":47,"to":47,"h":185,"unit":43},"Line 2","25-30",{"type":38,"l":187,"from":41,"to":41,"h":185,"unit":43},"Line 3",{"type":38,"l":189,"from":190,"to":190,"h":191,"unit":43},"Line 4","line4","21-30",{"type":38,"l":193,"from":194,"to":194,"h":185,"unit":43},"Line 5","line5",{"type":45,"l":46,"from":40,"to":47,"unit":43},{"_":197,"notBefore":50,"notAfter":198,"evidence":52},"Roman imperial in date",300,[200,203],{"_":201,"type":56,"ref":202},"Syracusae","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462503",{"_":71,"type":60,"ref":204},"http://sws.geonames.org/2523083",[206],[207,208],37.08415,15.27628,[210,211],37.0784545,15.2786827,{"_":73,"role":74,"ref":75},{"_":214,"type":78},"15083",{"_":80,"mainLang":81,"languages":216},[80],{"n":218,"url":219,"height":220,"width":221,"desc":222,"surfaceType":223},"screen","ISic001871_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Parco archeologico e paesaggistico di Siracusa, Eloro, Villa del Tellaro e Akrai, and the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2022-04-29.","front",[],[85],[89],[228,229,230,15,170,23,231,100,98,99,100,101,102,81],"isic001871","funerary inscription for gamike",{"_":12},"syracusae","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Γαμική\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Γαμική\">Γαμική\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"χρη\n                    στὰ\">χρη-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>στὰ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">καὶ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἄ\n                    μεμπτε\">ἄ-\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>μεμπτε\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χαῖρε\">χαῖρε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζη\n                    σε\">ἔζη-\u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>σε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔτη\">ἔτη\u003C/span> κς´ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":234,"ptr":235,"ref":236,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},"400",{"target":107},{"_":109,"target":109},{"file":238,"uri":238,"title":239,"status":240,"editionAuthor":13,"type":241,"objectType":242,"material":243,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":244,"handNote":248,"date":265,"places":266,"geo":269,"provenance":201,"provenanceGeo":271,"country":69,"region":70,"settlement":71,"repository":272,"idno":273,"textLang":274,"tmNumber":26,"facsimile":276,"letterHeights":278,"publications":279,"zotero":280,"keywords":281,"html":285,"bibl":286},"ISic001872","Funerary inscription for Mousa",{"_":12},{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},{"_":170,"ana":171,"ref":172},{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},{"layout":245},{"p":246,"rs":247,"damage":26},"Text over six lines, set in a recessed panel in the style of a temple facade, but without guidelines. Some use of interpuncts and vacats in the text.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"lettering":249,"dimensions":250},"Text is deeply incised in letters of slightly varying size. Extensive use of serifs, with several letters tending to the cursive. Alpha has straight bar, curving ends; epsilon is lunate with equal length mid-bar; zeta is large and curved; kappa has near full-length arms; mu has slanting strokes that reach the lower line, but often join before the top and have extended upper strokes; pi has overlapping cross bar; rho has closed eye; sigma is lunate. Elegant hedera in line 2; use of vacats in age at death.",[251,253,255,257,258,260,264],{"type":38,"l":134,"from":40,"to":40,"h":252,"unit":43},"25-31",{"type":38,"l":184,"from":47,"to":47,"h":254,"unit":43},"20-22",{"type":38,"l":187,"from":41,"to":41,"h":256,"unit":43},"19-25",{"type":38,"l":189,"from":190,"to":190,"h":256,"unit":43},{"type":38,"l":193,"from":194,"to":194,"h":259,"unit":43},"19-21",{"type":38,"l":261,"from":262,"to":262,"h":263,"unit":43},"Line 6","line6","20-21",{"type":45,"l":46,"from":40,"to":47,"unit":43},{"_":197,"notBefore":50,"notAfter":198,"evidence":52},[267,268],{"_":201,"type":56,"ref":202},{"_":71,"type":60,"ref":204},[270],[207,208],[210,211],{"_":73,"role":74,"ref":75},{"_":214,"type":78},{"_":80,"mainLang":81,"languages":275},[80],{"n":218,"url":277,"height":220,"width":221,"desc":222,"surfaceType":223},"ISic001872_tiled.tif",[],[85],[89],[282,283,284,15,170,23,231,100,98,99,100,101,102,81],"isic001872","funerary inscription for mousa",{"_":12},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μοῦσα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Μοῦσα\">Μοῦσα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χρηστὰ\">χρηστὰ\u003C/span> ❦ \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">καὶ\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\">ἄμεμπτε\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χαῖρε\">χαῖρε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζη\n                    σε\">ἔζη-\u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>σε\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"μῆνες\">μῆνες\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ι´ ·\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> ἡμέρας \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> κε´ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":234,"ptr":287,"ref":288,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},{"target":107},{"_":109,"target":109},{"file":290,"uri":290,"title":291,"status":292,"editionAuthor":13,"type":293,"objectType":294,"material":295,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":296,"handNote":304,"date":317,"places":318,"geo":321,"provenance":201,"provenanceGeo":323,"country":69,"region":70,"settlement":71,"repository":324,"idno":325,"textLang":326,"tmNumber":26,"facsimile":328,"letterHeights":330,"publications":331,"zotero":332,"keywords":333,"html":337,"bibl":338},"ISic001873","Funerary inscription for Kopria",{"_":12},{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},{"_":170,"ana":171,"ref":172},{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},{"layout":297},{"p":298,"rs":299,"damage":26},"Text over five lines, neatly respecting gridlines to the base of each line and with marginal lines to left and right - that on the left is approximately followed, that on the right is ignored; an additional gridline below is unused. Some use of interpuncts and vacats in the text. The first line shows clear traces of red paint in the letters.",[300,301],{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"_":302,"ana":303},"rubrication, red colour","#execution.rubrication.red",{"lettering":305,"dimensions":306},"Text is incised in fairly tall, thin, neat and plain letters mostly without serifs. Alpha has downward left sloping cross-bar; epsilon is lunate, with shorter and sometimes detached middle bar; zeta is straight; eta sometimes has detached cross-bar (line 4); kapa has short arms; mu has angled strokes, the mid-strokes only descending half-way, and no upward extension of the apexes; omicron is slightly smaller than other letters; pi does not overlap; rho i slcosed; sigma is lunate. Use of a simple/stylised hedera in lines 2 and 4, and letters are somewhat irregularly spaced especially in the final line.",[307,309,311,312,314,316],{"type":38,"l":134,"from":40,"to":40,"h":308,"unit":43},"29-30 (omicron = 20)",{"type":38,"l":184,"from":47,"to":47,"h":310,"unit":43},"26-32",{"type":38,"l":187,"from":41,"to":41,"h":185,"unit":43},{"type":38,"l":189,"from":190,"to":190,"h":313,"unit":43},"24-30",{"type":38,"l":193,"from":194,"to":194,"h":315,"unit":43},"22-32",{"type":45,"l":46,"from":40,"to":47,"unit":43},{"_":197,"notBefore":50,"notAfter":198,"evidence":52},[319,320],{"_":201,"type":56,"ref":202},{"_":71,"type":60,"ref":204},[322],[207,208],[210,211],{"_":73,"role":74,"ref":75},{"_":214,"type":78},{"_":80,"mainLang":81,"languages":327},[80],{"n":218,"url":329,"height":220,"width":221,"desc":222,"surfaceType":223},"ISic001873_tiled.tif",[],[85],[89],[334,335,336,15,170,23,231,100,98,99,100,101,102,81],"isic001873","funerary inscription for kopria",{"_":12},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Κοπρία\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κοπρία\">Κοπρία\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χρηστὰ\">χρηστὰ\u003C/span> ❦ \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">καὶ\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\">ἄμεμπτε\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χαῖρε\">χαῖρε\u003C/span> ❦ \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζη\n                    σεν\">ἔζη-\u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>σεν\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔτη\">ἔτη\u003C/span> λ´ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":234,"ptr":339,"ref":340,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},{"target":107},{"_":109,"target":109},{"file":342,"uri":342,"title":343,"status":344,"editionAuthor":13,"type":345,"objectType":349,"material":353,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":354,"handNote":358,"date":459,"places":464,"geo":467,"provenance":201,"provenanceGeo":469,"country":69,"region":70,"settlement":71,"repository":472,"idno":473,"textLang":475,"tmNumber":477,"facsimile":478,"letterHeights":481,"publications":482,"zotero":490,"keywords":498,"html":502,"bibl":503},"ISic003331","The Syracusans honour King Gelon, son of Hieron II",{"_":12},{"_":346,"ana":347,"ref":348},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":350,"ana":351,"ref":352},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},{"layout":355},{"p":356,"rs":357,"damage":26},"Three lines of finely carved Greek letters, centred on the stone (line one with short vacats at beginning and end, line 2 fully filling the face of the stone, line 3 centred with substantial vacats before and after.",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"lettering":359,"dimensions":448},[360,361],"Elegant wide and very regular letters with thinly carved strokes. Broken bar alpha; beta with equal sized loops; epsilon with short middle bar; kappa with short arms; mu with vertical first and last, middle strokes to half-height; omicron normally full size but small in line 2 (compression a factor); rho with almost fully rounded eye; sigma with approximately horizontal top and bottom strokes or very slightly open; omega full-size rounded and open with straight feet.",{"_":362,"ref":363},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                 